OL,3,CJersey Ministers consider standard
OL,4,Chourly rate for 'care at home'
OL,6,FSocial Security Minister Deputy
OL,7,FLyndsay Feltham says the government
OL,8,Fhas taken a "very common sense"
OL,9,Fapproach.
OL,11,FShe adds: "I know that some in the
OL,12,Fcare sector have been waiting for this.
OL,14,F"They've been waiting for the packages
OL,15,Fthat we pay to be level and equal and
OL,16,Ffair, but I hope that we can all work
OL,17,Ftogether to provide the type of care
OL,18,Fpackages that our community needs."
