OL,3,CJersey Ministers consider standard
OL,4,Chourly rate for 'care at home'
OL,6,FHowever, it may mean some businesses
OL,7,Fwill take a financial hit if their
OL,8,Fcurrent standard rate is higher than
OL,9,Fthe change, and some residents are
OL,10,Fconcerned about the future of their
OL,11,Fcare.
OL,13,F95-year-old John Rae says his age and
OL,14,Fdisability prevent him from being
OL,15,Fcompletely independent.
OL,17,FHe explains: "It's very important
OL,18,Fbecause (carers) help me a lot -
OL,19,Fdressing and undressing and things
OL,20,Flike that. They are very good."
