OL,3,CJersey Ministers consider standard
OL,4,Chourly rate for 'care at home'
OL,6,FJohn has paid for carers for years
OL,7,Fthrough the long-term care fund, but
OL,8,Fthe company he uses is charging more
OL,9,Fthan the standard rate being
OL,10,Fintroduced.
OL,12,FHis son, Marcus, explains: "The only
OL,13,Fdownside we found is the time it took
OL,14,Fto find a care provider that could
OL,15,Fwork at the rate that they were
OL,16,Foffering.
OL,18,F"He's not going anywhere in a hurry,
OL,19,Fso it will be a bit of a stretch to
OL,20,Ffinance the long-term care."
